Dorsum. Derm membranous, apart from an incomplete sclerotised crescent around anal plates on old adult females (
Fig. 1
). Dorsal setae entirely absent. Preopercular pores (A) round, concave with a granular surface in centre, each 5 . 6 m wide, present in a single medial longitudinal line anterior to anal plates (total number of pores: 4244 ). Other dorsal pores of 2 types present, all distributed in same area as preopercular pores: (i) simple pores (B), circular, each 2.5 m wide, inserted between preopercular pores; and (ii) minute microducts (C), each about 0.5 1.0 m wide with a long narrow inner ductule, with same distribution as simple pores. Anal plates (D) elongate, each sub-triangular with inner margin diverging posteriorly; dimensions of each plate (m): 5575 m wide, anterior margin 6085 m long, posterior margin 7890 m long, inner margin 100130 m long; each plate with two spinose setae along inner margin, each 4852 m long, plus an apical seta 53 m long, and a discal seta of same shape and size. Ano-genital fold with 3 or 4 pairs of setae on lateral margin. Anal ring with three pairs of long setae.

